    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted at Medium assurance level. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted based on regulatory precedent for ASTM F1717 as the standard single-condition submission protocol and the conservative nature of the 35 mm offset configuration. All quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) satisfied across all three QoIs and all 11 validation specimens. The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for predicting compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct within the defined COU.",
